# Pet Protector Map Maker - Project Plan

This document contains the finalized implementation plan and task list for the Map Maker tool.

---

# Implementation Plan

Create a dedicated web-based map editor to support infinite-scale, layered maps with decoupled item definitions.

## Proposed Changes

### Data Architecture
We will transition from a single JSON map to a modular, chunk-based system.

#### [items.json](file:///c:/Users/lauri/Documents/Repos/random-stuff/pet-protector/web/data/items.json)
Definitions for all items in the game.
- Decouples emoji/name from logic effects.
- **Effects**: Can affect `hydration`, `energy`, and `nutrition`.
- **Example**: `apple: { name: "Apple", emoji: "🍎", effects: { nutrition: 20, hydration: -5 } }`.

#### [Map Config](file:///c:/Users/lauri/Documents/Repos/random-stuff/pet-protector/web/maps/manifest.json)
Global map settings.
- **Version**: Increments on manual save.
- **Spawn Points**: A list of `{ name, id, x, y }` (defaults to "Spawner #").
- **Zones**: A list of `{ name, id, tiles[] }` with behavior settings.
- **Warps**: Transition points `{ name, id, targetMap, targetPos }`.

#### [Map Chunks](file:///c:/Users/lauri/Documents/Repos/random-stuff/pet-protector/web/maps/chunks/chunk_0_0.json)
Layered tile data (32x32 blocks).
- **Tile Structure**: `{ base, item, zone, warp }`.
- **Base Tile**: ID referencing an asset-ready definition (e.g., "grass_v1" which maps to a sprite/color).

---

### Robust Persistence System
To prevent data loss and allow easy restoration.

#### Auto-Save (Action-Based)
- Every edit is automatically saved to `<map_name>_tmp/` (a directory containing the current chunks and manifest).
- UI displays "Time since last auto-save".

#### Manual Save (Atomic Safe Promotion)
To ensure zero data loss from failed renames/deletes:
1.  **Version Bump**: Increment the `version` number in the manifest.
2.  **Preparation**: If `<map_name>_old_del/` exists, delete it.
3.  **Backup**: If `<map_name>_old/` exists, rename it to `<map_name>_old_del/`.
4.  **Rotation**: Rename current `<map_name>/` (the master) to `<map_name>_old/`.
5.  **Promotion**: Rename `<map_name>_tmp/` to `<map_name>/`.
6.  **Initialization**: Create a new `<map_name>_tmp/` directory based on the new master for future edits.
7.  **Cleanup**: Delete `<map_name>_old_del/`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Unit Testing**: All save/rotation logic must be covered by unit tests to guarantee safety.

### Map Maker Application
A separate web app located in `pet-protector/map-maker/`.

#### UI Component
- Sidebar with tool palettes (Ground, Items, Zones).
- Main viewport using PIXI.js for high-performance rendering of many tiles.
- Property editor for selected tiles/zones.
- **Search & Snap UI**: Sidebar lists for Spawners, Zones, and Warps with a "Snap" button to center the viewport on them.
- **Status Bar**: "Time since last auto-save" display.

#### Map Maker Logic
- Viewport management (pan/zoom).
- Painting logic (single click, drag, fill).
- Item Definition editor (ability to add new items like "Fish" or "Golden Apple").
- Zone drawing tool.
- **Transition Point (Warp) Tool.**
- **Action History**: Implementation of Command pattern for `Undo/Redo` (Ctrl+Z/Ctrl+Y) support.
- **Deployed Maps Manager**: 
    - Lists all maps in `map-maker/maps/`.
    - Shows "Current Version", "Old Version", and "Deployed Version".
    - Highlights maps where "Current" > "Deployed".
    - "Deployed" checkbox to sync with `pet-protector/web/maps/`.
- Export to JSON (Chunks + Manifest + Items).

---

### Game Engine Updates (Phase 2)
The game engine will be updated to fetch chunks dynamically based on camera position.

